issue.body:
The following assert in `TestPlanScannerFilterTests` does not seem to make sense.

``` java
    @Test
    void emptyClassAccepted() {
        assertTrue(newFilter().accept(EmptyClass.class), "accepts empty class because it is a container");
    }
```

In this case, when you debug into `TestPlan.countTestIdentifiers`, it will return true because the test plan contains the two root identifiers for the Jupiter and the Vintage Engine. Since `EmptyClass` is empty, it should not be accepted by the filter.

## Overview

Fixes #508 by replacing logic behind `isTest()` and `isContainer()` from two independent boolean properties into an enumeration based one:

```java
enum TestDescriptor.Type {

	ENGINE, CONTAINER, TEST, CONTAINER_AND_TEST;

	public boolean isContainer() {
		return this == ENGINE || this == CONTAINER || this == CONTAINER_AND_TEST;
	}

	public boolean isTest() {
		return this == TEST || this == CONTAINER_AND_TEST;
	}
}
```

Convenient and code duplicate remover methods `TestDescriptor.prune()` and `TestDescriptor.pruneTree()` are introduced.

